about1:
well; not that it is very easy to write about oneself but lets give it the best shot (let me know if i get the Bookers prize for writing well). Jokes apart but here it goes.... My mom tells me i have chakras on the soles of my feet (meaning that people with chakras travel a lot). I was born in Visakhapatnam and was brought up in Jamshedpur (You are right.. the steel city). After completing my schooling i studied my graduation in Agra and Post graduation happened in Gangtok (Sikkim). My first job took me to Hyderabad. I moved on from hyderabad to Gurgaon for my second job and then to Mumbai and back again to Gurgaon. And thanks to my job profile i have to be frequently travelling (an average of 10-12 days a month)
i am a strong believer in GOD (though not orthodoxly religious), confident, willing to take on challenges in life (at both the personal and professional front). As much as i am career oriented i am a firm believer that the women is the 'home maker' and family always comes first for me. i love to listen to good music (actually i am a versatile listener and can appreciate everything from M S Subbalakshmi to Pearl Jam... and that also without linguistic barriers)
i love photography (somewhat passionately), cooking (reasonably well, my frinds have survived my culinary experimentation :-)) and driving (currently enjoying my Maruti Zen) My family is also a third generation Dayalbagh Satsangi- you may have to get in touch with me or my parents to understand this because not much can be written about this in this column.
